===Noun===
'''{{PAGENAME}}'''  (''plural:'' '''[[rakije (Sr.)]]''')
Strong alchool drink made from fruit. In English closest equivqlent is "whiskey". "Rakija" is general name for short and strong drinks made of fruit. Most frequent "rakija-s" are shlyvovica ("šljivovica", made of plum, lozovacha "lozovača", made of grapes' leftovers, yabukovacha "jabukovača", made of apple, and so on). The name used mostly in Serbia, Croatia and Bosnia.

